-- Karstadt to Reduce Electronics, Fashion Offerings, FTD Reports
-- B y   A l e x   W e b b
-- 2012-02-29T03:00:01Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2012-02-29/karstadt-to-reduce-electronics-fashion-offerings-ftd-reports.html
Karstadt Warenhaus GmbH plans to
reduce its range of merchandise to simplify its business model,
 Financial Times Deutschland  reported, citing an interview with
Chief Executive Officer Andrew Jennings.  The department store chain, which is owned by investor
Nicolas Berggruen, will no longer sell entertainment electronics
and will reduce its fashion offerings, FTD said.  To contact the reporter on this story:
 Alex Webb  in Frankfurt at 
